This license applies only to the Original Components contained in /releases/ and its first-level subfolders within this repository. It does not apply to any files outside /releases/.

A) Definitions
1. "Licensor" means IT’s Secured.
2. "Original Components" means all files, folders, and artifacts located under /releases/ and its first-level subfolders in this repository.
3. "You" means the individual or legal entity using the Original Components.
4. "Private Use" means use by a natural person for non-commercial, personal purposes.
5. "Non-profit" means a legally registered non-profit organization using the Original Components solely for non-commercial purposes.
6. "Business/Commercial Use" means any use by a for-profit entity or any use intended for commercial advantage, revenue, or internal business operations, including (without limitation):
   - use in a product or service offered for a fee,
   - use in a business workflow or internal system,
   - use by consultants or contractors for paying clients,
   - distribution as part of a commercial offering.
7. "Author Block" means the exact attribution text in /releases/NOTICE (and, if present, /releases/docs/AUTHOR_BLOCK.txt).

B) Grant of Rights
Subject to the terms below, the Licensor grants you a non-exclusive, worldwide license to use the Original Components as permitted in Sections C and D.

C) Free Use Grant (Private + Non-profit)
You may use the Original Components for Private Use or Non-profit use without payment, provided you comply with the Attribution Requirement in Section E and all other terms.

D) Business/Commercial Use Grant (€100 one-time)
If you intend any Business/Commercial Use, you must pay a one-time fee of €100 (one-time) per legal entity before use.
After payment, you may use, modify, improve, and redistribute the Original Components, provided you comply with the Attribution Requirement in Section E and all other terms.
Payment instructions are provided in /releases/PAYMENT.md.

E) Attribution Requirement (Author Block)
You must preserve the Author Block in all copies and in all substantial portions of the Original Components.
Removing or altering the Author Block, or distributing the Original Components without the Author Block, automatically voids this license.

F) Prohibited Actions
You must not:
- remove, alter, or obscure the Author Block,
- claim authorship of the Original Components,
- use the Original Components outside /releases/ without a separate license.

G) Termination (Automatic Voiding)
Any breach of this license automatically terminates your rights. Upon termination, you must stop all use and distribution of the Original Components. Sections E, H, I, and J survive termination.

